trans-unit.source: Represents a collection of parameters relevant to an <xref href="System.Data.Odbc.OdbcCommand"></xref> and their respective mappings to columns in a <xref href="System.Data.DataSet"></xref>.
This class cannot be inherited.
The number of parameters in the collection must equal the number of parameter placeholders within the command text, or else the .NET Framework Data Provider for ODBC raises an error.

Use caution when using this overload of the <xref:System.Data.Odbc.OdbcParameterCollection.Add%2A> method to specify integer parameter values.

Because this overload takes a `value` of type <xref:System.Object>, you must convert the integer value to an <xref:System.Object> type when the value is zero, as the following C# example demonstrates.

``` parameters.Add("@pname", Convert.ToInt32(0)); ``` If you do not perform this conversion, the compiler will assume you are attempting to call the <xref:System.Data.Odbc.OdbcParameterCollection.Add%2A?displayProperty=fullName> overload.
